The paper deals with a geometric problem of covering a line segment with intervals, which suggests that it could belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) category. The problem also involves minimizing distances, which is a common theme in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The application of the problem in wireless sensor networks suggests that it could also belong to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) category. Finally, the problem involves optimizing movements, which could be relevant to control systems and robotics (cs.SY).
